Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.34,0:00:18.32,Lucy-Song-Title,,0,0,0,,[I want to be a rainbow]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.59,0:00:29.77,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa hoshifuru yoru ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.02,0:00:36.71,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono tomoshibi wo keshi wa shinai to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.98,0:00:47.83,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa akane no asa ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.08,0:00:56.77,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wakaba ni somaru haru wo yobou to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.04,0:01:08.66,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Ono utsu hibiki michi hiraku utagoe
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.93,0:01:20.44,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kodama ga mune ni hazunde kuru no
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.82,0:01:26.38,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono oosora no niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.66,0:01:36.18,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kibou ni todoku niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.59,0:00:29.77,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow I made on that starry night
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.02,0:00:36.71,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To not let this flame die
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.98,0:00:47.83,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow made on that brilliant red morning
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.08,0:00:56.77,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To call out for spring, dyed with young leaves
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.04,0:01:08.66,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,Cutting axes open up roads, under the sound of singing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.93,0:01:20.44,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,The echoes bounce around in my chest
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.82,0:01:26.38,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow in this big sky
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.66,0:01:36.18,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow that reaches out to hope
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.35,0:01:47.31,Lucy-Ep-Title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(320,306.667)\fade(295,285)}Ep. 38 - Lucy, the Detective
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.61,0:01:48.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Never!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.30,0:01:54.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Anything... Anything but this! I can't give this up!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.49,0:01:59.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Move away from it!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.36,0:02:01.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I can become very mean\Ntowards those who disobey me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.52,0:02:07.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Master! It can get very dangerous, Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.73,0:02:08.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.45,0:02:10.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Never! I absolutely won't move away!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.03,0:02:11.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.64,0:02:14.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I take it you don't need your life, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.65,0:02:21.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't step away by the time I count to ten,\NI'll drop the courtesies and do away with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.84,0:02:23.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.57,0:02:24.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Kate, I'm scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.98,0:02:26.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a threat...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.82,0:02:27.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm scared!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.13,0:02:34.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The stagecoach that Lucy and me took to get home\Ngot assaulted by a gang of tree robbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.13,0:02:41.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Pettywell, carrying a bag, and his servant Adam boarded the same stagecoach as we.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.05,0:02:42.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.78,0:02:43.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eight.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.26,0:02:45.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Nine...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.78,0:02:46.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.13,0:02:49.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They shot me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.96,0:02:52.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.44,0:02:56.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What now? You should've done that\Nfrom the very beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.10,0:02:58.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Master, are you hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.74,0:03:01.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... No... No...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.45,0:03:03.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! I recovered the bag!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.51,0:03:04.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How's it going over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.51,0:03:07.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,All done except these children.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.41,0:03:09.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Children shouldn't have any money on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.93,0:03:12.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You never know.\NEveryone did their part.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.76,0:03:14.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! You do your part too!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.60,0:03:17.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But we don't have anything with us...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.21,0:03:18.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't lie to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.41,0:03:19.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.48,0:03:22.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Please take this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.31,0:03:23.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hm? What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.73,0:03:24.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Marbles.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.89,0:03:26.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.09,0:03:29.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Those are the marbles that I value very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.74,0:03:30.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Take them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.31,0:03:32.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Get it away, you idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.55,0:03:34.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,These brats are making fun of grown-ups!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.97,0:03:38.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! We've no time to play with some children now!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.54,0:03:42.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We've got the king's ransom.\NThe sooner we make a getaway - the better! Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.20,0:03:43.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.33,0:03:48.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.70,0:03:51.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Dammit! That bag...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.34,0:03:55.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ladies and gentlemen!\NThanks for cooperation. And now, farewell!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.35,0:03:56.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Giddyup!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.78,0:04:01.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it! Damn it all! Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.00,0:04:06.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Master, it's not money, but your life...\NYour life is what matters the most!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.31,0:04:10.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! The money! 50,000 pounds! Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.18,0:04:13.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We should let the police know as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.49,0:04:16.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They took away my diamond ring!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.01,0:04:18.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's leave it to police to catch those goons.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.99,0:04:22.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Either way, we need to return to Adelaide first.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.46,0:04:25.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Do we really have to walk all the way on feet?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.21,0:04:29.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you, do something already!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.74,0:04:33.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you say so, that'd be quite problematic.\NOnly god knows where my carriage is by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.58,0:04:37.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's return to the road and see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.80,0:04:42.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Kate.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.96,0:04:43.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.73,0:04:45.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.22,0:04:46.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.51,0:04:49.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The robbers left already.\NThey won't come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.21,0:04:50.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's not that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.26,0:04:51.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? What, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.41,0:04:54.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Master. Get yourself together, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.27,0:04:58.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Adam, whatever it takes,\Nwe gotta get that money back...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.76,0:05:01.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose... It was 50,000 pounds, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.10,0:05:03.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,50,000 pounds!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.15,0:05:09.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,W-What's wrong, Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.73,0:05:12.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This is strange.\NMighty strange, I would say.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.50,0:05:14.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,W-What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.20,0:05:19.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How did those robbers know\Nthe bag had money inside, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.71,0:05:21.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.80,0:05:24.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That was because they saw me\Nholding it as something valuable.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.50,0:05:29.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, those guys didn't look inside the bag even once.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.17,0:05:33.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, I clearly heard him saying,\N"There's a king's ransom inside."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.62,0:05:35.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,D-Do you think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.34,0:05:40.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Without ever looking inside the bag,\Nthese guys knew there's a huge sum in it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.79,0:05:41.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why's that, Adam?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.99,0:05:45.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Eh... Well, how am I supposed to know that, huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.87,0:05:48.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.20,0:05:49.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.63,0:05:56.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! I found the carriage!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.80,0:05:59.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Look, it's over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.39,0:06:03.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Thank goodness.\NEveryone, I'll get the carriage back to here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.27,0:06:05.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Wait there for just a moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.80,0:06:16.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,At least, it seems you won't have to walk\Nall the way to Adelaide. Aren't you glad, Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.79,0:06:22.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,After I just gave 50,000 pounds to robbers,\Nwhat's there to be glad about, you imbecile?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.58,0:06:25.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... I'm awfully sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.19,0:06:28.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.82,0:06:31.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.74,0:06:33.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.00,0:06:35.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You've been going on "scared, scared"\Nfor a while now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.19,0:06:36.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.90,0:06:38.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.41,0:06:40.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I saw it all!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.38,0:06:44.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. The time is not specified, but Master\Nwould be bringing the money in the afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.38,0:06:46.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure there's no mistake, Adam?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.84,0:06:48.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Is he bringing along that stupid bulldog too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.79,0:06:49.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.25,0:06:52.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What did you see, Lucy?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.20,0:07:03.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I can't say.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.96,0:07:06.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I can't say it now. I'm too scared!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.57,0:07:12.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.00,0:07:19.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Hey! Who do you think you are\Nto stop your stagecoach in front of the police station?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.91,0:07:21.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I-It's bandits!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.56,0:07:22.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.21,0:07:26.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,While passing though the Hindmarsh Prairie,\Nwe got robbed by three goons!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.76,0:07:32.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eh... Seems like I ended up staying for pretty long.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.55,0:07:35.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, that drink was good too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.61,0:07:39.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you stay and have\Ndinner with us too, Doctor Deighton?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.27,0:07:41.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, no, you've spoiled me enough as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.06,0:07:45.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no. You needn't be shy, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.00,0:07:46.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome home.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.16,0:07:47.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.03,0:07:48.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right, welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.71,0:07:53.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, you're in luck. I'm coming home\Nwith a fresh loaf of delicious bread today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.55,0:07:56.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, I was actually just about to have my leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.42,0:07:57.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.32,0:07:58.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, goodbye, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.99,0:08:01.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, please be wary of the robbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.58,0:08:03.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What? Robbers?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.62,0:08:07.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. They say a stagecoach was robbed today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.50,0:08:08.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.68,0:08:10.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Clara, at what time did it happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.52,0:08:14.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just now. I saw that robbed carriage\Nin front of the police station myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.64,0:08:16.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It was a stagecoach going to the port.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.49,0:08:17.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.60,0:08:19.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.53,0:08:23.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know what happened\Nto the passengers of that stagecoach?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.11,0:08:24.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Should be at the police station now...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.24,0:08:27.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, was someone killed or injured?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.79,0:08:30.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows. But tell me,\Nwhy are you so inquisitive about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.94,0:08:35.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you see, it's possible that Kate and Lucy\Ntook that stagecoach, Ms. Clara.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.95,0:08:36.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.97,0:08:40.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ben stopped by today and took those two to the port.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.90,0:08:42.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.30,0:08:44.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to the police station.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.20,0:08:47.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Where's father?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.20,0:08:48.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I have to apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.62,0:08:53.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He was drinking with me, but the fellow drank\None too much and is sleeping now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.21,0:08:56.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Father... Was very thoughtful of him\Nto do that at such a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.60,0:09:09.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey. Marsh, don't bother me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.49,0:09:19.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's why...\NThat's why, Inspector Clark,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.43,0:09:23.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,the initial objective of those robbers\Nhave been me and my 50,000 pounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.83,0:09:25.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm convinced it's so.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.70,0:09:29.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gradually coming to see it this way too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.03,0:09:31.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Still, one part of it just doesn't sit well with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.79,0:09:35.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How exactly it doesn't sit well with you?\NThat's the only possible explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.14,0:09:40.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Supposing that as you say, Mr. Pettywell,\Nthe robbers' objective had been your money,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.90,0:09:48.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How did the robbers know\Nyou would be riding that stagecoach?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.78,0:09:49.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.49,0:09:53.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're saying that your own carriage broke down,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.19,0:09:56.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,so you and Adam had to ride a stagecoach\Ncompletely by chance, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.73,0:10:01.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,T-That's right! How could they possibly know\NI would be riding that stagecoach?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.10,0:10:04.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I believe, I have the answer to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.29,0:10:06.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? You do?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.20,0:10:08.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So what is your answer, Inspector Clark?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.59,0:10:14.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The breakdown of your carriage was prearranged\Nwith the intention of getting you to ride a stagecoach.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.48,0:10:16.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.48,0:10:20.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But then, why would those robbers\Ngo to such great pains?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.90,0:10:24.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why not just assault my own carriage directly?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.91,0:10:27.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's exactly it. That's one thing I can't figure out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.00,0:10:31.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,A while ago you said you saw something\Nthat you were very scared of, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.49,0:10:32.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.50,0:10:34.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What did you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.59,0:10:36.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me, what did you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.61,0:10:39.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Today, on my way back from school...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.31,0:10:40.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.20,0:10:43.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,On my way back, I climbed a tree, and then...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.05,0:10:44.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.41,0:10:49.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right, sorry to have kept you waiting.\NEveryone else can now come inside too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.67,0:10:52.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, little ladies, sorry for the delay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.30,0:10:56.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Unless there's anything important you could tell us,\Nyou two can return home now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.41,0:10:58.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's getting pretty late, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.27,0:11:01.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy, you have something you could tell, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.55,0:11:03.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? You have something?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.41,0:11:08.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.56,0:11:10.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, you're free for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.89,0:11:21.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy! Kate!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.01,0:11:23.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.83,0:11:26.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.54,0:11:30.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.80,0:11:39.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now, then. You two sure been\Nthrough some scary stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.35,0:12:06.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, we've arrived to the mansion.\NCome out, Silver!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.89,0:12:11.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, make it quick, please.\NI'm tired from walking all day!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.30,0:12:24.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So Mr. Pettywell lost 50,000 pounds, isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.89,0:12:27.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It has to be it, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.39,0:12:35.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, Lucy. This is a very important point to make,\Nso I want you to tell us once more to be sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.35,0:12:39.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure the person\Nyou saw under the tree was Adam?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.39,0:12:41.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, no doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.38,0:12:44.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, there was also the other man\Nwho called him Adam.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.50,0:12:46.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Alright. Let's sum it up, Lucy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.05,0:12:51.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You believe Mr. Pettywell's servant Adam\Nwas an accomplice of the Robbers, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.11,0:12:55.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Besides, in order to separate Mr. Pettywell\Nfrom his bulldog, he sabotaged the carriage,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.90,0:12:58.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,so that Mr. Pettywell would have to take a stagecoach.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.50,0:13:00.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you tell any of this to the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.96,0:13:04.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever I looked at Adam's face,\NI was getting awfully scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.35,0:13:08.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, what if the police doesn't believe my story...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.60,0:13:13.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose. No, don't get me wrong,\Nusually, I wouldn't doubt whatever Lucy says.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.20,0:13:16.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But this story right here\Nis not backed by a single proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.90,0:13:18.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.10,0:13:21.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The police would surely\Nwant to see some proof, won't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.00,0:13:25.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I believe it! And I think we'd best\Nretell this story to the police. 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.03,0:13:26.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I think so too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.53,0:13:30.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even if there's no telling what the police\Nwould make of it, I'll go there now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.76,0:13:48.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps I've been a little too rash, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.46,0:13:49.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If you think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.60,0:13:54.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,the prospect of Mr. Pettywell's long-time servant being in cahoots with the robbers is too unrealistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.77,0:14:00.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,When I told the whole thing\Nto the inspector, he snubbed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.13,0:14:02.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But Lucy isn't the kind of child to be telling lies.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.92,0:14:08.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the person Lucy saw passing below\Nwhile climbing the tree was most certainly Adam.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.40,0:14:10.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But that's pretty much all we have.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.48,0:14:12.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't really think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.21,0:14:15.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, we gotta watch our step from now on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.62,0:14:21.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If we call Adam a robber without any solid proof,\Nthat'd be the most outrageous thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.97,0:14:24.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You there, Lucy? Come in for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.09,0:14:28.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector Clark is an idiot for not believing my story.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.94,0:14:30.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.40,0:14:33.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Father, you believe me, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.80,0:14:38.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. But you know, without the evidence,\Nthe police can't take any story seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.70,0:14:39.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.90,0:14:52.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad returned, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.69,0:14:59.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even if nobody believes me, I'll do it on my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.77,0:15:02.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll find the evidence that he conspired with robbers!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.00,0:15:04.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll help you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.31,0:15:17.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Have a good day.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.11,0:15:30.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Without relying on anyone else, Lucy-May
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.61,0:15:33.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,made up her mind to find that evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.10,0:15:40.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,She figured, if she'd keep watch on Adam, one day,\Nhe'll go meet with his accomplices to get his share.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.29,0:15:41.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.30,0:15:50.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, I also came to help her with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.67,0:15:54.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We'd take turns in keeping watch,\Nand at times, even did it together.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.89,0:16:01.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder who that was.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.40,0:16:03.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure it was a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.45,0:16:07.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way he'd ask Dr. Deighton for help, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.02,0:16:10.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Of course! Not after he's been\Nmistreating him that badly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.90,0:16:14.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But if they needed a doctor to come,\Nthat means someone's ill, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.25,0:16:21.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor Smith has arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.71,0:16:24.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you bring me a doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.44,0:16:26.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well... It was the Madam.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.23,0:16:31.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't need no doctor. Only the recovery\Nof my 50,000 pounds would cure me immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.79,0:16:34.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Are those Robbers not captured yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.70,0:16:36.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll invite the doctor into the room now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.90,0:16:38.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My 50,000 pounds...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.19,0:16:50.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Any abnormalities?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.42,0:16:53.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,None. The only one going in and out is Madam.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.65,0:16:54.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And Adam?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.71,0:16:56.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't go outside either.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.10,0:17:00.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, scratch that, he's going outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.40,0:17:18.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He's finally on the move.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.45,0:17:38.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder the robbers would really\Nset up their hideout in a place so lively.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.96,0:17:51.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This way is to the River Torrens.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.80,0:17:53.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,To our old house.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.44,0:18:10.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if Doctor Deighton\Nis the robbers' accomplice too?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.64,0:18:12.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't say such nonsense, Kate.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.09,0:18:15.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What now? You again? Need something from me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.65,0:18:18.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Your time is finally up, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.80,0:18:22.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow, or the day after tomorrow at most,\Nplease vacate the house, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.55,0:18:23.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Never!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.46,0:18:27.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we've no choice, then.\NWant us to tear this house down with you inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.17,0:18:28.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You don't mind that, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.60,0:18:31.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Seems like he just came to tell Dr. Deighton\Nto move out from the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.99,0:18:47.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Going back already?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.72,0:18:49.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So we were following him in vain?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.70,0:18:54.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute. He stopped on his way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.87,0:19:08.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He's going towards the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.69,0:19:13.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This time, is has to be it! He's going there to meet\Nwith his accomplices. Now, let's hurry after!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.28,0:19:16.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Wait! If we get too close, he'll spot us!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.19,0:19:28.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He's going to that cabin, doesn't he?\NOn the riverbank.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.99,0:19:30.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Seems so. That must be it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.90,0:19:33.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Things suddenly got interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.28,0:19:56.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.40,0:19:57.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's Adam!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.72,0:20:02.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sure no one saw you coming here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.78,0:20:03.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.80,0:20:11.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That cabin is where the robbers hide. I'm sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.26,0:20:17.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,S-So that really is where the robbers are hiding, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.32,0:20:21.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.82,0:20:24.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,W-We gotta call someone from the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.54,0:20:28.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Me and Little will stay here to keep a lookout,\Nand you go get help.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.55,0:20:30.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right. I'm going...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.40,0:20:35.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.82,0:20:36.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hold it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.73,0:20:37.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Shh.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.89,0:20:39.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector Clark?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.26,0:20:47.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The robbers are in that cabin, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.02,0:20:47.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.83,0:20:49.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And you must be Lucy?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.31,0:20:54.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to your testimony, we could put together that Adam was an accomplice of robbers. It was of huge help.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.44,0:21:00.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But Inspector, aren't you the type of person\Nwho wouldn't believe a child's story?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.60,0:21:06.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's just that I had to put on airs of disbelieving,\Neven if that was rude towards your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.25,0:21:10.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's why Adam, only slightly worried,\Npaid a visit to his buddies here so soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.15,0:21:14.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If Adam would've suspected that the police\Nwas on his tail, he'd panic and try to flee.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.30,0:21:19.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They came out!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.30,0:21:25.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it, they came out\Nmuch sooner than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.54,0:21:27.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The reinforcements haven't arrived yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.80,0:21:30.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You can count on Little's strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.73,0:21:33.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Little, you must drive those men\Nback into the hut.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.34,0:21:35.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.50,0:21:36.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.61,0:21:42.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What now? A stray dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.21,0:21:53.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Damn you! Such insolent dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.67,0:21:56.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.01,0:22:02.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I've had enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.47,0:22:14.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Splendid. Just splendid!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.61,0:22:24.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You there! We have you surrounded!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.59,0:22:28.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lay down your arms and come out!\NCome right out!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.38,0:22:37.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, all of the robbers were arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.10,0:22:41.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Nearly all of the stolen money\Nwas found with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.93,0:22:47.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.57,0:22:51.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Are you saying 100 shillings as my token of gratitude\Nare too few for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.12,0:22:53.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.36,0:22:57.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We're saying Lucy didn't do anything\Nthat'd warrant a gratitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.56,0:23:00.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I see, you're teaching your children to be humble?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.79,0:23:04.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, I don't suppose you mind\Nif I take these 100 shillings back?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.59,0:23:05.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Pettywell.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.98,0:23:07.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.20,0:23:10.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,To tell you the truth,\NI'd like to ask for a reward.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.61,0:23:11.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.67,0:23:15.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right, right, being honest like that\Nis the best way, Young Lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.05,0:23:17.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No. It's not about money.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.21,0:23:18.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.08,0:23:22.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,As a reward, I'd like to ask you\Nto not drive Dr. Deighton out of that house.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.46,0:23:27.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,"That house," you mean...\NDr. Deighton's clinic, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.44,0:23:29.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. Please do that for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.22,0:23:33.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That, I can't grant.\NThat train already left, young lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.45,0:23:34.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.94,0:23:37.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.61,0:23:39.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.40,0:23:48.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor Deighton was driven out of his brick house.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.49,0:23:54.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And so, he came to our house\Nto live with us once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.59,0:24:06.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor Deighton is going to the city of Gawler.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.78,0:24:11.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We won't see him again any time soon.\NBut then, there's one more sad parting on the horizon.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.31,0:24:14.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Next on Lucy-May of the Southern Rainbow:\N"Two Partings".
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.79,0:24:16.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
